[SN]TITLE[SN]
When should Burundi's traditional drums be played?

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The traditional drumming of Burundi is a symbol of national pride but a debate is being had about when the drums should be played.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
15 April 2015 Last updated at 17:07 BST
They were once reserved only for royal ceremonies but their use has expanded, and some drummers are asking for controls to be put in place.
BBC Africa's Salim Kikeke reports from Burundi.
